<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Otter_p0p</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Is there a Cleric out there who might be able to explain what the Word of Pain spell is AND in what situations I should use it in?<P>Thank you.<P>Dotekl <BR>Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">nightheron</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">the word of pain spells is a radius damage spell hits all targets within a close distance to you. you will get better raidus damage spells at higher levels. they are great for low hitpoints monsters in numbers or when you get swarmed and need to inflict damage on all of them at once. it's great when you get 3 clerics all casting at once and taking down 3-4 targets at a time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Veloran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Word of Pain is mana efficient if you're hitting 3 or more people. Don't waste your mana if there's just one or two creatures around you. Keep in mind that the closer the monsters are the more damage they'll take. WOP tops off I believe around 28 or so. Once you get Smite at 14, you probably won't use WOP that often.<P>Very important, because this is an AOE spell, don't cast this around friendly NPC's or guards. Let's just say this won't make them too happy. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Cirdec</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">It should also be kept in mind that any mob that isn't already engaged when you cast any area spell will immediately turn on the poor cleric who was only trying to help!  Tough to heal when you are being whomped on by 3 or 4 crits <G></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Goldhealer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">at level 19 clerics get an upgrade to WOP...  Word of shadow<P>at level 29 they get Word of Spirit<P>at level 39 they get Word of Souls<P>and I am not sure beyond that except at level49 they get Word of Divine....  it is an Area effect divine aura spell<P>Goldhealer </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Caffin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hello<P>I was wondering if the upgrades to wop were worth it.  I got wop and was not impressed..in fact it got me in more trouble than it was worth.  Is the damage on Word of shadow worth it?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hurk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Word of pain is a step back, i hated it It does more damage, but is more Inefficiant than word of shadow.Word of spirit and up is worth it. The damage done to the mobs is not adjusted by range; they are either in range and take full damage(or partialy resist) or they are out of range and are not affected. The word line is replaced by the earthquake line, which has a much larger radius of affect. The key to these spells in not to use them unless you have a damn good reason. I do zone patrol (train killing) in unrest and use these spells to pull all the mobs off the victim and on to me. In most casses, if the mobs are too powerful, I will have to zone too(its hard to cast with six mobs beating you). In the case of lower level trains though, this spell at spirit level and above, can sometimes wipeout two or three, and send others running. I used Spirit in CrushBone the other day, and it was a hoot. Of the 12 mobs brought to the zone a pawn and three centurians died instantly, two centurians and two legioneers ran, Dvinn, Crush, The royal guard, and a Legioneer stayed to fight. After several unsucessful attemts to cast, I finally got a second off killing eveything but Dvinn(others were helping tough). I then had to zone because of the damage I'd taken, and knew I couldnt get a good heal off with Dvinn pounding me. I use these spells when I know there are lots of small mobs Mixed with the ones I want to fight (like unrest). I DO NOT use this spell to fight multiple mobs my own level. Id rather root and back off one or two, or have my enchanter mesmerize the extras. This way, if you are knee deep and you call for help, those that come can actually take the mobs off you.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Griner</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I use WoP a lot!  I am lvl14 now and have spent a lot of time in West Karana fighting bandits in groups.  It relly helps a lot when my group gets real close together and then I cast this 2 or 3 times and then go med until I need to heal.  This only works for me when I am with others who can taunt the MOBs off me.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Arss Rubybone</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Another good time to use the area effect spells is when u want to finish off a kill and at the same time add some additional dam to the other mobs.<P>Be prepared to pay the consequences tho. If ur tanks are not worthy u will take some revenge damage from time to time.<P>I havent used the AE line of spells that often.  Generally, i find it more efficient to Heal and use my Major blast spells occasionally when i need to drop a nasty that can dish out more dam than i can heal.<P>Arss Rubybone<BR>L30 Cleric<BR>Norrath Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Frens</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">The best use for WoP, I've found, is to give your group enough time to get the hell out of there.  If you suddenly find your 4 member group under attack by 10 mobs, you will pull at least 6 onto you with WoP.  Divine Aura has a trivial casting time, just get it off as soon as possible and your friends can get to the zone.  As to your fate, well, I'm sure your group will compensate you for the experience loss.<P>------------------<BR>Frens<BR>Forge-junkie<BR>"I can heal ya... let me get my hammer and a file."<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Kromb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Actually a good heal will be better when it's time for your group to zone. Every monster not engaged will attack you so you can Divine Aurua and train. Chances are if you need to run someone needed that heal anyay. Remember heals are taken into account for who the mob will attack. If someone hit a mob for 30 hps and you healed for 90 guess who the beast thinks is doing more damage to its chance of surviavl.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
